
Overview of noun pony

The noun pony has 5 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (2) pony -- (a range horse of the western United States)
2. (1) pony -- (an informal term for a racehorse; "he liked to bet on the ponies")
3. pony, trot, crib -- (a literal translation used in studying a foreign language (often used illicitly))
4. shot glass, jigger, pony -- (a small glass adequate to hold a single swallow of whiskey)
5. pony -- (any of various breeds of small gentle horses usually less than five feet high at the shoulder)
